</p>
<p>Now, make that AJAX call! I'll use <code>$.ajax()</code> with <code>url</code> set to <code>previewUrl</code>. Chain
a <code>.done()</code> to add a success function with a <code>data</code> argument. And <em>just</em> to try
things out, open sweet alert with a message: <code>Total $</code> then <code>data.total</code>, since the
endpoint returns that field:</p>
